casebody.data:
No. 3253. Venable & Heyman v. Chavous,

November Term, 1893.

December 5, 1893, J. J. Brown, for the motion. J. L. Tobin, contra.

This was an order

per curiam;

of refusing to reinstate an appeal dismissed by the clerk under Rules 1 and 2, “neither unavoidable causes for the default of the appellant nor mistake or inadvertence having been shown.”-
